HEADWORD: Eventilate
<hw>E*ven"ti*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>eventilatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>eventilare</ets> to fan. See
<er>Ventilate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To winnow out; to fan.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To discuss; to ventilate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eventilation</ent>⟦br⟧
